Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.67,0:00:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And so each one represents a level of consciousness.\NWe first presented the levels of human consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.11,0:01:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that integrity, the major one to worry about is 200.\NOnce you get over 200, the rest is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People are already worrying about what their level of consciousness is.\NThe only thing of any concern is whether you're over 200 or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.60,0:01:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because the rest has a thousand karmic propensities\Nand has to do with motivation, has to do with a multitude of factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.58,0:01:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention, however, drives you through the levels of consciousness\Nand the work that's involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.36,0:01:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lifetime, it was extraordinary, the amount of work at times,\Nand at the other times, extraordinary in that they were spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.60,0:01:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and not preceded by any work.\NSo there's no predictable cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.65,0:01:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A person says, I've been doing these mudras,\NI've been doing these hand positions,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.53,0:01:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been doing these breathing exercises,\NI've been doing the meditating, and I'm not getting anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.43,0:02:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, instantly his consciousness level just jumped.\NHe was trying to artificially control, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.09,0:02:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Artificially control your level of consciousness\Ninstead of just letting it be that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.13,0:02:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which is kindly, considerate, humorous.\NSee the humor in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great blessing.\NSome people cry in agony all the way to the chopping block.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, me, they're chopping my head off today, you know.\NEasy come, easy go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As an old head chopper, I was telling them,\Nit's only going to hurt for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only going to hurt for a second.\NDon't worry about a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.60,0:02:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.\NWhat I just stated is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.27,0:03:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.\NI wasn't lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In one second, no more pain, no more suffering.\NThere's a body and this dopey head rolling around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.99,0:03:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The French peasants are jumping up and down with glee.\NThat's why they call them peasants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.96,0:03:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the French aristocracy thought.\NPeasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one then is a way of perceiving the world, perceiving yourself.\NIt has to do with a certain level of energy and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.38,0:03:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the degree to which the kundalini energy,\Nhas become dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.88,0:03:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, there's the classic chakra system,\Nin which the spiritual energy is envisioned as flowing up the chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Which again, is really analogous rather than a literality.\NNobody ever measured it, except us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to say, nobody ever measured it,\Nand then I realized we're measuring it all the time, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.93,0:04:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the level of consciousness, then, is what the number denotes.\NIt does not mean better than.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.26,0:04:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what appeals to you, at a given time in life,\Nmay be quite different than what appeals to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.52,0:04:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and becomes meaningless later.\NProbably the spiritual teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.68,0:04:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with the most popular impact,\Nare those that probably calibrate in the mid-200s,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the 700s.\NWe go, ooh and ahh at 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the people who teach goodwill,\Nhonesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.36,0:04:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I'm a fan of the Boy Scouts,\Nthe Boy and Girl Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:05:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Scouts calibrate around 460, or somewhere around there.\NThe Scouts calibrate around over 450,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.62,0:05:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,460,\N455.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scouts calibrate at 455.\NSo instead of going all the way to India and seeking Guru Ba-Ba-Drum-Drum,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I suggest you join the Scouts.\NThe Scouts are at 455,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.57,0:05:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Guru who used to be high, is now,\Nyou know, at 140,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.37,0:05:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and sleeps with everybody.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.40,0:05:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,have holy sex, right.\NThings that people can sell themselves, hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.92,0:05:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, an integrous teaching of a lower number.\NSo what you see often attracts people to more advanced teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the glamour of the more advanced teacher.\NIt's just the glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality, like anything else, can become a glamour,\Nlike popularity, like money, like titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.93,0:06:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just glamourized.\NOh, he calibrates at 70 to 95.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.93,0:06:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Except you don't know what the hell he's talking about.\NThat's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too helpful if you don't know what the person means.\NYou know, Ramana Maharishi says,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.00,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in lamenting the world,\Nor intervening, or trying to do something about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world you see doesn't even exist.\NIt's all perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true in the level 700.\NBut it'd be a spiritual error not to do something to help the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.76,0:06:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're calibrating at 260.\NAnd you have your choice between service towards others or selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The world you see doesn't even exist,\Nbut that is so at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not so at 250.\NKatrina, or Kachina, or whatever the name of that horror hurricane was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,tornado, whatever that thing was,\Nknocked down a zillion people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.65,0:07:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo your perception of it then is reflection of your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you feel called to do depends on that.\NYou cannot be false to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be true to yourself.\NYou see yourself as a fellow human.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.44,0:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do what I can to be helpful.\NThen that's what you're called upon to do at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at a different level,\Nand you see this karmic consequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a group karma,\Nand nothing to do with individuals or causality or anything like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.92,0:07:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can do nothing about it.\NBut it's not so until it's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.53,0:07:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not so until it's so.\NSo we can't be false to ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.53,0:07:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own self be true means,\Nhowever you see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.53,0:07:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is what your obligation is.\NSo our karmic obligation is dependent on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.72,0:07:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,our culpability\Nand responsibility are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.72,0:07:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility is one thing.\NCulpability is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:08:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility is a karmic given.\NIf you take somebody's life, you owe a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.45,0:08:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's independent of culpability.\NCulpability has to do with the degree of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If the child pulls out a gun from his parents' dresser drawer\Nand shoots somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,his culpability is zero.\NBut he is accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.55,0:08:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And he will have to pay back the life in another life.\NWhat I just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.96,0:08:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He owes a life.\NKarmically, you owe a life because you took a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.64,0:08:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the culpability may be zero.\NAnd even the courts recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.73,0:08:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the degree of responsibility.\NAnd the imbecile, the so-called retarded person, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is seen to be operating under impaired responsibility.\NAnd therefore, their culpability is less.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.73,0:08:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they are still accountable.\NSo if you make a pledge, you're accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is what you pledge,\Nthen this is what you give
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:09:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,if you leave that particular group.\NThat's the oath you took.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,\Nwe've tried to include some,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.42,0:09:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the most easily recognized.\NThere are some more popular,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which I have on another list,\Ncurrently alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are popularizers of spirituality.\NPopularizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.42,0:09:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often they're a good place to start.\NBecause they get you excited about the whole subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give you a place to start.\NSome of them are extremely well known, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.87,0:09:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Pot and Jelly, 715.\NHow do you pronounce his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.12,0:09:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Patanjali or Pot and Jelly?\NNobody here knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.82,0:09:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We in Dyer calls them Pot and Jelly.\NAnd I was thinking of them as Patanjali.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.82,0:10:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so,\Nwe see Father Pio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.04,0:10:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio, you know,\None of the ways he exhibited the cities was
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by location.\NTo be several places at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.26,0:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course that would sound very odd to a skeptic.\NAnd the skeptic dictionary didn't approve of Father Pio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because such a thing is beyond linear probability.\NBeyond linear probability.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been two places at once.\NBut you can disappear time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.63,0:10:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYou can disappear distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.63,0:10:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By letting go, resisting the experiencing of time.\NI used to do it routinely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.92,0:10:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Driving from Phoenix to Sedona.\NWhich is very boring after you've done it a couple hundred times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:11:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And by letting go, resisting the subjective experiencing of time.\NWhich you do continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.62,0:11:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as a thought.\NBut you feel the experiencing of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.62,0:11:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you let go, resisting it.\NBecause you're impatient to get to Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's late at night, etc.\NIf you constantly let go, resisting the experiencing of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.75,0:11:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,time disappears.\NAnd all of a sudden within a minute you're in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.97,0:11:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you leave Phoenix at 10.01 and at 10.03 you're in Sedona.\NSubjective experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to do it routinely.\NSo you can use these kind of techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of resisting.\NOf anything that you find onerous or difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.10,0:11:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of resisting of anything.\NEven the subjective experiencing of time itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.10,0:11:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even let go of resisting your own existence.\NThat's one you can save.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.87,0:12:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting your own experience.\NBecause the delusion is, if you don't keep recreating it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you will come to an end.\NAnd that's what it means that the self is reborn every split second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That unless you intend the continuation of your own existence,\Nyou will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NThat you, what you think is the you, will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstatically to an end.\NEcstatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.26,0:12:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so you can disappear time.\NNow you can see you can disappear the resistance to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is your oyster.\NAnything you want you can let go of resisting having money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.90,0:12:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that.\NLet go of resisting having money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.73,0:12:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting the wanting to have money.\NBe crazy to have money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:13:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Go insane to have money.\NLet go of resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.33,0:13:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally you say, no one needs money, right?\NSo who needs it anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.59,0:13:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You let go of it.\NAnd then suddenly your aunt leaves you a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell this story in the book about Greta.\NYou know what I told Greta?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.20,0:13:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who came over from Ireland without a nickel.\NI don't know how far she got in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixth grade.\NWent to work for one of the most famous rich families in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lived in the Locust Valley around where I live.\NAnd they hired her as a bookkeeper, as a housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.32,0:13:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And Greta was so integrous and so dedicated to the family and the children.\NI think I told this story before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.06,0:13:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That at dinner time the old man would give her tips on the stock market.\NTake your hundred dollars Greta and invest it in a Zanza.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.24,0:13:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It would triple within a week, of course.\NBecause it was insider training, illegal nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I had somebody come to me one time and he says,\NLook, give me $10,000 and I'll make it go up ten times within 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.24,0:14:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I know what this company is going to do.\NI turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.56,0:14:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pure and poor.\NWhat did you do with my teachers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So at each level you get attracted to certain things.\NSo which teacher is meaningful to you is many factors including many unknown karmic factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.16,0:14:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that Father Pugh represents first of all the background of Catholicism.\NSo some of the teachers represent the emergence and most mystics emerge beyond many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:15:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A large number that are well known to the world.\NEmerged out of various religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.45,0:15:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest level of awareness is always the mystic.\NEven though the mystic is a member of a certain religious organization or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.96,0:15:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic who shoots over a level 600 does so by becoming the truth from within.\NAnd may or may not hang around the religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.88,0:15:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In which this arose later on.\NBut it's merely the setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's mystics in every religion.\NEvery major religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic is one in whom who has followed the evolution of consciousness such as we've described.\NAnd now the truth shines forth of its own radiance from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.33,0:15:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not acquired as a book learning or a memorization.\NIt has nothing to do with liturgy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with ecclesiastic approval.\NIt has to do with an inner awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have done severe physical exertion to the point of exhaustion.\NI give the example I've given.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan has had the experience.\NYou push yourself to the absolute limit beyond which you cannot go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.61,0:16:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be an endeavor such as walking barefoot across the desert.\NWhatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.84,0:16:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You push yourself to the limit beyond which you cannot go.\NAnd now you refuse the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.02,0:16:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you shoot past the impossible.\NAnd you move into the incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.88,0:16:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what I call the Roger Bannister effect.\NYou push the human endurance past to the level that science says you cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.24,0:16:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you refuse.\NYou refuse with an iron like savage will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:17:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when it's time to get yang.\NThe time to get yang is when you run up the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.24,0:17:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You run up against the I can't.\NAnd that's when you crash through the I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.40,0:17:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly you're in a different dimension which is effortless.\NAll the boxes that you couldn't lift anymore are now weightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember being in that warehouse exhausted after 12 hours of work and that heat.\NI cannot lift another box.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was like gritting your teeth and all of a sudden it was effortless.\NThe body was like feather.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The boxes lifted themselves.\NAnd dawn, it went all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.48,0:17:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn was there and they said, you haven't been to bed yet?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.48,0:17:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The same happens when you go into a state of ecstasy where you can dance effortlessly hour after hour.\NAnd those cities are available to any spiritual student.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.69,0:18:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They arise as an opportunity to exceed the limitation.\NBecause the limitation is the belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.13,0:18:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're only subject to what you hold in mind, then you have a belief that you're limited.\NThat you can only lift so many boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.45,0:18:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That you've been so many hours without food.\NYou've been so many hours without water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it's not physically possible to continue on.\NThat's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is possible to continue on.\NNot you as a person, but your beingness can go on because your beingness is unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.16,0:18:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It can keep on working and working and working.\NSo these are things we hear about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.16,0:18:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio's miraculous things.\NWe hear about the great saint, Saint Patrick, that launched Christianity in Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, he's very famous.\NAnd corned beef and cabbage was named that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.18,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yogananda is extremely well known.\NAutobiography of a yoga.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has a place started in California.\NSome of the other teachers come from other cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're not familiar with them.\NHowever, their writings are extremely familiar to many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.69,0:19:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Yogananda himself.\NAnd he was a fun guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he used to take these orange hats and throw them in the audience.\NDuring the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there would be a crowd around him.\NAnd the crowd knew that his energy was in the orange hats.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So he had a pile of orange hats.\NHe'd wear one for five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he'd throw it in the audience.\NAnd everybody would take it home because they knew his energy was in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,His energy at that time was 655.\NBut met Yogananda anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.32,0:20:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fun.\NSo what I'm trying to say is the spiritual evolution is progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It should bring you into progressive joy.\NIt's not the same thing as piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.05,0:20:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Piety and saintliness is a very nice thing.\NEspecially when you're on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.37,0:20:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the robes sway nicely.\NAnd your sandals go clip-clop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now those are distortions of reality.\NBecause spiritual integrity is very, very, normally, honestly, that which is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.54,0:20:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to pretend to be anything else.\NIt is exactly what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.54,0:20:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's so completely satisfied with that which it is.\NIt doesn't have to imitate that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.54,0:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Which it is not.\NSo one thing we'd say about these teachers, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:21:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they all represent an intrinsic integrity\Nwith nothing to gain, nothing to sell, no desire to control anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.08,0:21:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha recommended enlightenment\Nas a way to avoid the pain of reincarnation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.18,0:21:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and going through the pain and misery of humanness.\NGetting born and dying, sickness, old age, poverty and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.33,0:21:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm recommended too.\NBecause at a certain point you don't care about sickness, old age, poverty and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's irrelevant.\NYou've got an apple for dinner, what more do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a cot to sleep on, there's a wooden box.\NAnd the only thing is the big desert centipedes do crawl around
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.10,0:21:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and give you a little heebie-jeebies once in a while.\NBut other than that, poverty is perfectly fine, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.10,0:21:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever you need arises out of the occasion.\NIt arises not as a matter of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:22:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It emerges as a consequence of the occasion.\NSo we're going to stop now so that we have more to talk about later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.10,0:22:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to make the afternoon a little shorter as far as the lecture goes.\NSo we have more time for questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.58,0:22:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to see us eventually move into workshops\Nthat are a lot of interaction with the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.64,0:22:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of, you know, it grabs you to, you want me to explain more about that?\NYou say, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.64,0:22:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more about that?\NIn which we become more spontaneously interactive with each other, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.64,0:22:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And get away from this artificiality that the teacher up there\Nand us down here, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's actually all of us here, isn't it?\NSo I'd really like people to, I'd really, the best way I'd like to teach
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.64,0:22:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would be to wander through the audience and people spontaneously bring up\Nwhat is coming up in the field, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.64,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you people are the field and all these heads here\Nare picking up the thoughts and the feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:23:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's, you know, the teacher is what's sitting in the chair.\NThe teacher, this is just the responder to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.64,0:23:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way I'd like to teach is wander through the audience\Nand people just pop up with whatever they got and they answer back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.64,0:23:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That will drive Robert crazy, but the man in the wall says the mechanics of that\Nare difficult and the TV people, of course, they also say that's difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle the mechanics.\NJesus didn't have that problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.71,0:23:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The great saints of old didn't have to get focused on TV\Nand turn up the volume on the recorder, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.77,0:23:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But they served a different function.\NBut now that you see the speed of spiritual evolution is very rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.77,0:23:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And one is mass media, one is people here by the thousands.\NThat which was only heard by a dozen favorite people years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.87,0:24:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's available to everyone.\NSo I'll conclude with this finality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.87,0:24:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances of becoming enlightened today are over 1,000 times greater than in the past.\NOver 1,000 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.87,0:24:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just confirm that.\NOver 1,000 times. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.51,0:24:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can get off the excuse that it's very, very rare.\NAnd therefore it doesn't apply to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.28,0:24:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay for me to not be enlightened because it hardly ever happens.\NThat was then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is now. Get busy.\NWe're all here because we're all here because we're all here because we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.11,0:25:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Serious spiritual work, it's hard to remain serious.\NWhy? Because you're constantly confronted by absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.57,0:25:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, absurdity.\NPerception versus essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.83,0:25:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you put the two together, you get humor, you know.\NYep. Where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.57,0:25:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, right.\NIntegra spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.88,0:25:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's great popularization of spiritual fiction.\NAnd the naive students and people who are interested in spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.68,0:25:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,think that's what spirituality is.\NYou know, best sellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.68,0:26:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing that I don't like about them is they don't make it clear that it's fiction.\NAnd they state it as though it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.64,0:26:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly a saint appears next to you, you see.\NAnd that's, you know, it's a writer's fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.77,0:26:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a reality.\NThat is not the reincarnation of St. Patrick or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.41,0:26:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's all kinds of spiritual fiction.\NAnd people get it confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.41,0:26:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And the spiritual fiction is also the lure for the child within\Nwho likes the imaginative and the fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.41,0:26:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more fantastic the climb, the bigger the sales, you'll notice.\NJesus and Mary were married and their children became the aristocracy of France
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.63,0:26:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and all such BS.\NThe trouble is the naive seeker considers that truth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.40,0:26:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's an interesting book out called Odd Gods.\NOdd Gods by James Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.40,0:26:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Odd Gods and the Cult Phenomena.\NIt's a pretty thick book.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.49,0:27:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing I like it...\NThat is funny, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.49,0:27:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a pretty thick book, yeah.\NBooks of spiritual truth are slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.00,0:27:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What I like about it is he gives you many examples.\NAnd by the examples, you get the drift of it, how it comes about.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.77,0:27:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see what it attracts.\NIt attracts the innocent child with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.77,0:27:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Within us who like magic and fantasy and the fantastic.\NSo many things that are called, considered by the populace, the spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.77,0:27:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are really, you know, the fantastic.\NHarry Potter books, at least, you know, it's clear from the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.77,0:27:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you're talking about a trueness story.\NBut these books, you know, I know that people take it serious
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.00,0:27:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because some highly intelligent people write me long dissertations about this.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.03,0:27:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,About what's the one with the painting from my...\NDa Vinci.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.44,0:28:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Da Vinci, yeah, right.\NNo end of the Da Vinci crap I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.44,0:28:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Emails and stuff.\NI mean, no end, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.79,0:28:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why I calibrated some of it for the book\Nbecause I want to point out to people there's spiritual fiction
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.79,0:28:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's spiritual reality, you know.\NThe reality doesn't sound as appealing as the fantasy and the fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.79,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Which appeals to the romantic.\NSo within us all is the child and the child's curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.79,0:28:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the child's naivety, impressionability, and people become misled.\NSo where were we on the slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.85,0:28:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We were someplace or other.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.88,0:28:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we wanted to go over those.\NThese, of course, this is 144, plus I got another 20 here,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.17,0:28:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which I've lost someplace.\NThey're more contemporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.68,0:29:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But this should do, you know.\NYou just take one and follow it through,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.35,0:29:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and that'll take you to 605,\Nso you don't need another book until you get past 605.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.48,0:29:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you just do the one thing consistently.\NAll right, so the thing, the magic of spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.57,0:29:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually consistency.\NSincerity, of course, integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.70,0:29:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But the consistency with which you do it.\NSo you could say, well, I heard, you know, from the doc the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.96,0:29:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you just let go, resisting, experiencing the passage of time,\Nyou go outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.99,0:29:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it may take a while to do that.\NYou may continually do it and continually do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.31,0:29:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean the first time you do it, it's going to work this fast.\NBut if you persist in it, let go resisting the passage of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.53,0:29:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let go resisting it, let go resisting the passage of time,\Nlet go resisting it, let go resenting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.53,0:30:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you go outside of time.\NAnd within no time at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.07,0:30:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you find yourself back in Sedona on the scene.\NSo all of these things take a certain persistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.74,0:30:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because there's a certain karmic momentum.\NI don't call it, you're not determined by karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.74,0:30:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I call them propensities,\Nwhich you inherit once you have an etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.92,0:30:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is your spiritual history encapsulated, you might say,\Nin a vibrational form,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.92,0:30:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is a propensity.\NBut it's not predetermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.92,0:30:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma doesn't mean predetermination.\NKarma means propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.31,0:30:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the evolution of consciousness is over very long periods of time.\NVery long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.72,0:31:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the evolution of one's consciousness,\Nconsciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.12,0:31:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain point, as I say,\Nis that you remember previous lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.12,0:31:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it may happen spontaneously,\Nor there's various techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.57,0:31:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The only time I think it's really important,\Npast life recall,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.57,0:31:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is if you are stuck with something.\NAnd I say the way to get out of a stuckness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.73,0:31:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is see what's happening in your life,\Nlet's say you're the victim of,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.73,0:31:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or picture yourself as the victim of,\Nwhat you pray for is the one within you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.12,0:31:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who did that to others.\NDon't bother praying for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.60,0:31:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a waste of time.\NPeople are always cheating me,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.25,0:31:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always getting, you know,\NI get them home and there's only ten eggs in the carton.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.00,0:31:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're always being shortchanged,\Nand always being taken advantage of by others,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.00,0:32:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then what you pray for\Nis the one in you who shortchanges others.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.00,0:32:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Always give it a 180.\NAlways presume that all the stuff in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.74,0:32:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want is the karmic consequence\Nof you having done it to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.74,0:32:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to believe it,\NI'm not asking you to believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.16,0:32:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just asking you to try it,\Nbecause it's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.64,0:32:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's rude to me.\NAlright, so, now you don't recall
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.64,0:32:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the one in you who's rude to others,\Nfor one thing you don't recall that lifetime maybe,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.80,0:32:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but the other thing you don't realize,\Nis that we collectively inherit
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.80,0:32:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness of mankind.\NCarol Young was correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.18,0:32:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a collective unconscious,\Nso even though you personally don't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.18,0:32:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,such a belief system,\Nnevertheless, you live in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.18,0:33:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you're getting programmed constantly.\NAlright, I never in my life believed in osteoporosis
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.40,0:33:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,affecting myself or men in general.\NI thought it was for little old ladies bent over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.40,0:33:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, if you're only subject\Nto what you hold in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.12,0:33:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then how can you get osteoporosis\Nunless you believed in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.63,0:33:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I personally never believed in it\Nas being the potential to afflict
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.63,0:33:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,this person here,\Nwho was all very vigorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.04,0:33:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a star dancer,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.04,0:33:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a star dancer.\NI could dance any dance, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.04,0:33:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That came out of a lifetime too once.\NAnyway, you pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.00,0:33:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I don't remember ever believing in it.\NYes, but you sat through a TV commercial
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.10,0:33:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all about osteoporosis\Nand taking this, that, and the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.10,0:34:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked it up, you picked it up.\NAlright, so just presume
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.23,0:34:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever is coming down in your life\Nyou picked up somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.45,0:34:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it so?\NWell, how do things come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.86,0:34:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They come about by the power of mind,\Nthat which you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.86,0:34:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as a belief system.\NYou see, the physical body is incapable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.73,0:34:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of experiencing its own existence.\NIt's only because of the senses
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.04,0:34:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're aware of what goes on in the body.\NYou're not experiencing the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.04,0:34:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're experiencing the sensations of the body.\NHow do you know the body is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.33,0:34:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the feelings.\NSo you're not even experiencing the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.33,0:34:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're experiencing the senses.\NThat's why the Buddha called the brain a sense organ.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.47,0:34:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the feelings have no capacity\Nto experience themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.53,0:34:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because there's something greater\Nthan the feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.60,0:35:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they can be experienced.\NAnd that is in consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.20,0:35:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is insentient.\NDo you know the body cannot experience anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.33,0:35:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is not capable of experiencing anything.\NExperience is of a different dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.33,0:35:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher dimension.\NThe body is not able to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.45,0:35:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,even that it exists.\NIt's because of feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.87,0:35:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And feelings are then,\Nbecause that's an awareness of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.87,0:35:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind can't know what it's thinking.\NIt's only because the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.96,0:35:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is in something greater than itself\Nwhich illuminates what the mind is thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.96,0:35:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,called consciousness.\NThat which you are then is the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.21,0:35:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all the sequence occurs.\NWhat is held in mind then begins to manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.30,0:35:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,within the physical body.\NSo if I develop osteoporosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.56,0:35:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I have picked it up somewhere\Nin our culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.75,0:36:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've picked it up from the collective mind,\Nor I'm holding it from some previous lifetime, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.22,0:36:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to get unhooked from some karmic probability\Nor potentiality likelihood,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.38,0:36:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if it keeps recurring in your life,\Njust give it an okay that it's likely
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.38,0:36:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a karmic propensity.\NAnd therefore do a 180 on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.40,0:36:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's shortchanging you,\Nthen you have to apologize
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.82,0:36:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask for forgiveness for the one in me.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.82,0:36:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I picked up an identification\Nwith the collective,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.82,0:36:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one who cheats others is part of you\Nby virtue of the collective unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.30,0:36:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the fact you identify yourself\Nas a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.30,0:36:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wham!\NYou just pulled in the entire karma
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.30,0:36:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of being human.\NSo there's the personal experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.36,0:37:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the personal past life,\Nwhich can be very, very specific,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.55,0:37:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way, very specific.\NOnce you learn how to rerun them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.74,0:37:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it's amazing how specific they are.\NYou see exactly what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.74,0:37:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the exact why of it,\Nand now you're empowered to undo of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.74,0:37:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,undo of it.\NAnd I remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.22,0:37:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know whether this, you know,\Nshare any past lives with you at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.67,0:37:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway,\NI remember one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.89,0:37:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never dance,\NI was Mr. Clubfoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.99,0:37:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was too inhibited.\NAnd one time in sort of a high state,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.02,0:37:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly recalled a lifetime\Nas a temple dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.34,0:37:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly I could dance.\NInstantly I became an expert dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.63,0:37:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I could dance any kind of dance,\Nand I still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.63,0:37:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretive, ballet, disco,\Nwestern.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.72,0:38:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was president of the country western dance club,\Nyou know, I was a dancing fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.04,0:38:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So once I learned how to dance,\Nthis frustration of my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.07,0:38:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I went dancing all the time.\NSo undoing the one karmic thing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.64,0:38:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,unleashed the capacity to dance.\NSo how would you have the talent
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.64,0:38:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to do all that kind of dancing?\NWhere would you get the talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.64,0:38:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was a very good temple dancer.\NI was a very excellent temple dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.64,0:38:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can still do temple dancing for you,\Nbut anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.84,0:38:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it came out of that lifetime.\NSo then once you're freed of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.84,0:38:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell right away\Nyou just got freed of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.84,0:38:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You just like know it.\NThat's sort of interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.87,0:38:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll tell you a few lifetimes\Nonce in a while just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.87,0:38:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the most important one.\NI forget the circumstances in which I recall it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.75,0:39:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shackled to oars.\NI was a slave on a slave ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.84,0:39:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And shackled with chains to the oar.\NAnd this guy who sets the beat,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.64,0:39:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I wasn't able to keep up with it.\NAnd he came over and started beating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.08,0:39:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's beating me.\NAnd I'll never forget the smell of that galley.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.08,0:39:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,God, it stunk because\Nyou got water running down behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.08,0:39:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're chained, you see, to this bar.\NAnd everybody just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.08,0:39:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,relieves themselves and the water\Nrushes in from the sea and washes it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.47,0:39:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I reached the point of absolute exhaustion.\NAnd I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.47,0:39:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was holding on.\NHolding on, holding on, holding on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.66,0:39:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And this guy was never going to stop beating on me.\NAnd suddenly it came to me out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.69,0:39:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in just that lifetime\Nthat I'm not a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.27,0:39:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not captured.\NAnd I let go of life, my physical life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.27,0:40:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly went into spirit and I was free.\NI cannot be enslaved because that which I am
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.62,0:40:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond the physical.\NAnd that knowingness came to me in that instant
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.62,0:40:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could let go.\NAnd there I was, free
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.42,0:40:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that pain and suffering and agony.\NWhat a happy spirit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.42,0:40:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Free, free, forever free.\NOkay, now we're going back to the spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.58,0:40:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And so those things come to you spontaneously\Nat a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.11,0:40:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're stuck with something,\Npresume that there's something behind that stuckness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.11,0:40:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And with a little research,\Nyou can sometimes find your way out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.11,0:40:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it sort of comes to you as a sudden flash.\NYou can say, dear God,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.11,0:40:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why I'm stuck with this.\NAnd dear God, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.11,0:40:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like your mudra,\Nyour way of being is a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.11,0:41:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask God for the miracle\Nof seeing what lies behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.62,0:41:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you get a vision.\NSometimes you get a rerun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.62,0:41:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's just a remark somebody says.\NI got an insight into something that came up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.62,0:41:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just at lunchtime.\NIt just came up spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.62,0:41:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, I can see why that happens.\NWhoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.62,0:41:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not the consequence of logical thought.\NSo being receptive,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.39,0:41:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,making your life for prayer,\Nis a very yin position,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.39,0:41:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,yin position, yin position,\Nin which you are open to divine inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.45,0:41:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like a quality of divinity\Nthat it cannot refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.87,0:41:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't arbitrary.\NIt's like it can't refuse
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.80,0:41:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the invitation when that supplication\Nis at a deep level of humility
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and absolutely genuine,\Nabsolutely genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.80,0:41:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the power of the yin.\NThe life, the worldly life imagines
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power all belongs to the yang,\Nto the masculine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.12,0:42:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the power belongs to the yin.\NA yin by this attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.12,0:42:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,can kill a thousand men.\NWhat did you do to kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.15,0:42:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I stood back,\Nand I allowed them to be themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.15,0:42:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they slaughtered each other,\Ndid they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.21,0:42:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in\Nemphasizing the advantage of one sex or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.04,0:42:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because they both have their own intrinsic style.\NMasculinity is a style,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.04,0:42:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and femininity is a style,\Nbut they're of equal power,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.04,0:42:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as any man knows.\NAll she does is go,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.22,0:42:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but honey,\Nwow,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.22,0:42:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,his day has just got changed.\NPuts away the golf bags,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.48,0:42:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,gets out the lawn mower,\Nmy mother-in-law is coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.31,0:43:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and look at the lawn.\NOkay, honey, don't be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.31,0:43:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All she did is raise an eyebrow,\Nisn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.31,0:43:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She raised one eyebrow,\Nshe changes the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.73,0:43:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's up there pushing and trying to make it all happen,\Nand she just goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.65,0:43:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so much for my view of the masculine and the feminine.\NAll right, so we'll go back to the written word here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.42,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to stop a little earlier today than usually,\Nbecause we're going to get more time for questions and discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.48,0:43:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was just ruminating, you know,\NI got to meet some of the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.12,0:43:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And Robert Monroe,\NMonroe is the Monroe Institute,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.12,0:43:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,teaches you in all your state of consciousness\Nwhere you can go out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.12,0:43:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I went out of the body spontaneously\Nlong before it was popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.41,0:44:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wrote about near-death experiences or out of body.\NIn fact, I was in psychoanalysis at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.83,0:44:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was deathly ill.\NAll of a sudden, I was out there in the middle of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.31,0:44:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The complete sense of who you are is there,\Nexcept for the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.31,0:44:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the physicality,\Nand I'll tell you it's very boring and not too attractive looking there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.31,0:44:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, every time you're out of body,\Nyou look at the physical body and you're like,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.31,0:44:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,\Nit's a really nothing experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.08,0:44:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But out of body, you know, you can think, feel, see.\NAll the senses are operative.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.08,0:44:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you about the time I went to the Monroe Institute\Nand learned how to go out of body at will.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.08,0:44:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I docked back in the body upside down,\N180 degrees out of phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.08,0:44:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking out the back of my head at the floor,\Nand I had to come out this way and go back in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.07,0:44:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Journeys out of the body.\NJourneys out of the body is a fun, fun book.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.10,0:45:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because nobody knew anything about such phenomena at that time.\NNear-death experience or out of body was not heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.48,0:45:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And Monroe began to spontaneously experience this.\NAnd he would have these amorous adventures,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he'd come back in his body with his wife,\Nand he'd be stricken with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.48,0:45:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very funny book.\NAnd he'd gotten into some lower astral realms
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.71,0:45:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and various places like that.\NSo when we did the Monroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.71,0:45:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and learned how to go out of body,\Nyou had to come back in the body at a whistle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.71,0:45:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like,\Nbecause people would get involved in various adventures
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.71,0:45:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in various astral realms.\NAnd so you had to make sure you were safe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.71,0:45:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,before they let you out there.\NSo they would train you how to get out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.71,0:45:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you were trained at the sound of this whistle\Nto come back in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.71,0:45:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how I shot back in the body\Nand discovered I was upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.16,0:45:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing about Monroe,\Nwho I think is deceased now,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.35,0:45:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he had the greatest voice I ever heard.\NIf you ever get a chance to get a tape
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.35,0:45:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or something by Robert Monroe,\Nhe had a sound of intrinsic peace within his voice
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that was just amazing.\NJust spoke from a level of absolute inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.73,0:46:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Really a mystical, incredible gift he had.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.83,0:46:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Muktananda I met, Monroe I met,\Nthe others are really from different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.17,0:46:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,different cultures,\Nand different times.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.17,0:46:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is probably the best known\Nbecause of Wayne Dyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.24,0:46:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Patanjali, he calls him.\NFather Pio is extremely well known also.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.46,0:46:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The last pope was at 570.\NI think this pope was at 565.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.46,0:46:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately the same.\NThe last pope was 570,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.62,0:46:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a saintly beneficence towards all.\NSort of a wholeness and oneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.62,0:47:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was, of course, quite saintly.\NPlotinus is also extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.77,0:47:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po, I think I spoke to you before.\NThe difficulty with Huang Po,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.77,0:47:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you follow him literally,\Nto negate the reality of the linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.77,0:47:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we've already covered,\Nyou will end up at the void,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.87,0:47:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 850.\NAnd the void is not where you want to end up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.93,0:47:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Many naive Buddhists,\Nin fact we get emails from,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.19,0:47:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,end up at 800,\Nwhich is the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.19,0:47:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the belief system,\Nthis is the outcome of a belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.32,0:47:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ultimate reality is nothingness.\NThat is a trap, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.53,0:47:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So he taught, you know,\Nto let go of belief,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.53,0:47:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,any belief or attachment in the linear.\NThereby you end up in,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.53,0:47:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,he presumed, in the non-linear.\NAt the time he wrote it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.66,0:48:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,he was at 850.\NAnd what he was talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.66,0:48:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have gotten complaints from email\Nabout people who landed in the void,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.66,0:48:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and now what?\NNo, the void is not the absolute state
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.88,0:48:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of nothingness.\NThe absolute state is allness, allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.88,0:48:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that differentiates the two\Nis that the ultimate state
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.64,0:48:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is filled and pervaded and predominant\Npredominantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.77,0:48:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,predominantly exquisite love\Nof an incredible quality beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.77,0:48:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no thingness\Nbut with the quality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.69,0:48:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the qualities of divinity.\NWe have a slide on that at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.30,0:48:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After he reached that state\Nin which he wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.46,0:48:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pathway of Negation,\Nhe himself discovered the error
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.10,0:48:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and went on to 960 before he died.\NBut he never wrote anything after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.10,0:49:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the last thing he wrote\Nis The Pathway of Negation at 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.55,0:49:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he himself went on.\NIt's very hard to write at those higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.44,0:49:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So he may have,\NI don't know how long before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.44,0:49:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but he discovered the ultimate truth.\NThe ultimate truth calibrates at 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.51,0:49:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothingness, the void, calibrates at 850.\NBut we've already mentioned that,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.51,0:49:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think I explained it in the book\Nthat's coming out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.54,0:49:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The error of a misunderstanding Hoang Po.\NRobert Powell, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.18,0:49:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is extremely well known.\NAll these Swamis are well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.21,0:49:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramakrishna is extremely well known.\NI remember Ramakrishna's state.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.31,0:49:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I went into the state that Ramakrishna described.\NAnd as I went into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.31,0:49:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew Ramakrishna.\NI was all alone in the chapel
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.50,0:49:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,here in Sedona at midnight.\NIn those days they didn't lock the chapel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.66,0:49:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The music stayed on all night.\NThe candles were on all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.85,0:50:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There weren't all the tourists that there are now.\NThe chapel was unlocked at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.85,0:50:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went in there to meditate\Nand went into an ecstatic state.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.17,0:50:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstatic state in which you could dance forever.\NYou could dance for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.17,0:50:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The dancing was\Nbecause of the exquisite joy of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.05,0:50:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the energy field of ecstasy\Nand it makes you tireless.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.56,0:50:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You could dance for hours.\NSo I danced all by myself in front of the altar
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.56,0:50:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to express my joy to God.\NEcstasy. Tireless.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.36,0:50:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the state described by Ramakrishna.\NSwami Ram Dass is not as well known by others,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.44,0:50:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have a number of books by him.\NAnd this is a different Sai Baba,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.44,0:50:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not Sathya.\NHe's a different Sai Baba.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.44,0:51:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lisa Sonella I met out in California.\NI believe he was
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.54,0:51:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a psychiatrist, I think,\Nand wrote about kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.54,0:51:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote about kundalini energy.\NSatya Dhananda also.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.73,0:51:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to meet a number of these people.\NSo Joseph Smith, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.73,0:51:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,started the major church.\NRudolf Steiner, well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.73,0:51:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Suzuki, of course,\Npopularized Zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.92,0:51:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Suzuki is the one that really made it well known\Nin the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.92,0:51:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa is 710.\NAnd this is another saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.12,0:51:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Saints, very often at higher levels of consciousness,\Npeople stop being socially active.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.40,0:51:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the majority drop out of society.\NA few manage to retain a function within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.40,0:51:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an adjustment that's hard to describe.\NIt's an adjustment that it seems to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:52:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of a divine commitment.\NIt's like a contract made prior to this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.50,0:52:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the fulfillment of this potential\Nwas part of the agreement,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.88,0:52:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or the contract, or the, yeah, whatever.\NWithout that, one disappears from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.15,0:52:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of the people who go over 600 leave the body.\N50%, once they reach 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.15,0:52:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,leave the body.\NAnd when you hit 600, you'll know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.15,0:52:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're invited to leave.\NIt's like invitational freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.44,0:52:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's recurred, you know,\Na number of times over the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.44,0:52:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one time it happened right in the middle of a lecture.\NI got to the end of the aisle,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.44,0:52:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the invitation to leave was very strong.\NYou could just leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.72,0:52:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you never know when it's gonna happen.\NSo whether you continue on in the world or not
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.72,0:52:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is really not up to any personal self.\NThere's nobody that thinks about it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.72,0:52:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and weighs the pros and cons\Nand decide I will do this or that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.72,0:53:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more or less the fulfillment of a potentiality.\NSo out of gratitude for divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.56,0:53:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for the awareness that has emerged\Nout of this awareness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.56,0:53:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of gratitude to God,\None then shares that for the good of that which God loves,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.56,0:53:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is all of us.\NLet's see, where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.84,0:53:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We were at, did you change this thing on me?\NWhat did you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.84,0:53:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what you've done.\NOh, Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.04,0:53:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We had Monroe.\NWe went down this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.04,0:53:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a Krishna.\NI get wandering off onto various people I've met.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.04,0:53:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few of them I didn't meet, you see.\NAnd Socrates, I'm looking forward to rejoining.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.04,0:53:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa, of course,\Nwas capable of the miraculous
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.16,0:54:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because she looked at the very pits\Nof the lowest level at which humanity can go
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.16,0:54:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and had the heart, the courage to look it in the face.\NVery few people can look it in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.42,0:54:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people can't even stand television or TV.\NThey can't even stand television depictions of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.42,0:54:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,much less look into the heart and soul of it.\NAnd I used to see that in patients brought in,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.74,0:54:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,bound up in wet cloths and all that.\NAnd the question would arise within consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.16,0:54:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what God do you wish of me?\NAnd there would be an opening of that soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.32,0:54:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,would open itself up.\NAnd in that second,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.32,0:54:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment had just occurred.\NAnd you could see the soul within was healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.32,0:55:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And now whether there was a social recovery or not\Nwas irrelevant because the moment had arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.32,0:55:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo that's what Mother Teresa did, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.32,0:55:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of these are extremely well known.\NEvelyn Underhill, Vivekananda, Alan Watts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.57,0:55:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The White Brotherhood, of course,\Nwas written about by Alice Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.31,0:55:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yaktusraya.\NA well-known teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.31,0:55:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can go to the next one, yes.\NIs this the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.17,0:55:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first one.\NAre we going backwards or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.39,0:55:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NDid I talk about these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.65,0:55:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NJames Allen, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.72,0:55:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,he's written a number of books written by Dove Press.\NRamesh Bhalsakar,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.20,0:55:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to spend some time with out in California\Nabout a week or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.20,0:55:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And Eva Sand is well known.\NWallace Black Elk.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.42,0:55:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NJacob Bohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.71,0:56:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard Bucky.\NThis he wrote, Cosmic Consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.71,0:56:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he was a physician.\NEric Butterworth, extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.96,0:56:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the origin of Calvinism.\NYou know, Confucius.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.22,0:56:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dalai Lama, like the Pope,\Ncalibrates about the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.22,0:56:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the head of a world church,\Nyou can't be really too high
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.57,0:56:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because all that would not be very interesting.\NBut 570, you're as saintly as you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.67,0:56:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and still function in the world.\NSo the Dalai Lama functions in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.67,0:56:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If he went on to 600,\Nhe would disappear from society.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.21,0:56:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all well-known teachers.\NThese are all well-known teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.21,0:56:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Meister Eckhart, of course,\Nis extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.21,0:56:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrated over 700.\NHe seems to me he gets too much into
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.69,0:56:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,discussion of the philosophy of theology\Ninstead of the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.69,0:57:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiential.\NTo me, the reality is the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.72,0:57:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be phrased subsequent to the experiential\Nrather than describing it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.72,0:57:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me the description should arise\Nout of the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.59,0:57:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is to suddenly go from frozen\Nwith the impossibility of dancing,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.16,0:57:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly.\NAll movement is spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.45,0:57:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I remember,\Noh yes, I remember the patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.77,0:57:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that come to me back then.\NAs a spiritual dancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.03,0:57:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what I did was I danced out a pattern.\NThe pattern was already in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.03,0:57:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The body merely imitated the pattern\Nwhich preexisted the movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.66,0:57:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So it came about spontaneously\Nas an acting out of the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.95,0:57:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember now as a temple dancer,\Nwhat held in mind was not the dance steps
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.95,0:57:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like choreography.\NNo choreography.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.95,0:58:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness of the pattern.\NAnd I become the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.04,0:58:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like a chromosomal,\Nthe chromosomal spiral about itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.43,0:58:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is a spontaneous event.\NNon-linear, in other words.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.49,0:58:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, Charles Fillmore.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.19,0:58:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Fillmores were very familiar with their work.\NOf course, we were on the,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.35,0:58:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would call a committee of the,\NI don't know, steering committee of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.18,0:58:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Unity.\NUnity, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.31,0:58:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NConsciousness research and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.31,0:58:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get to go to Unity\Nand it's a wonderful place to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.82,0:58:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we examined the original writings of the Fillmores\Nand calibrated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.04,0:58:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember?\NWe went up in the private library.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.14,0:58:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was locked and sacrosanct.\NThe librarian was just sort of speechless.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.14,0:58:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She wanted us,\Nso she kept pulling these things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.14,0:59:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And what beautiful handwriting.\NI mean, my mind is a scrawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.14,0:59:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is like script, you know.\NBeautiful handwriting and we calibrated that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.14,0:59:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we can recapitulate.\NI'm holding, okay, I'm holding,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.62,0:59:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm holding in mind calibrates over 800,\N850, 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.62,0:59:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We got about 900.\NThat as originally written by the Fillmores.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.75,0:59:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The original, if you ever get a chance to see it,\NI don't know if they let people see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.84,0:59:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That inspiration that came out of the heart of Christianity\Nradiated out at that incredibly high level,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.55,0:59:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which they then brought down into the 500s,\Nwhich is the level of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.55,0:59:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So they then were able to communicate\Nthrough the world at the level of 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.00,0:59:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which is comprehensible.\NYou can't really communicate with the world at 900 too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.06,0:59:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows what you're talking about.\NSo Emmett Fox, of course, is a great teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.48,1:00:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mahatma Gandhi,\Nwe wrote about he stood off the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.48,1:00:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The British Empire at the time they confronted Gandhi\Nwas coming from prideful militarism
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.48,1:00:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrated about,\NI forget what it calibrated now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.54,1:00:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote it in the book.\N190, I think, right, pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.15,1:00:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Gandhi calibrated 760.\NSo this is what I mean by standing up for truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.34,1:00:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he didn't wimp out.\NSometimes what's called spirituality to me
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.88,1:00:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is just wimping out.\NGandhi didn't wimp out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.46,1:00:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood for truth against the entire British Empire,\Nthe most powerful empire the world had ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.46,1:00:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was born, Britannia ruled the waves.\NOne-third of the globe was under the dominion
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.52,1:00:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the British Empire.\NAnd this skinny little 90-pound Indian,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.23,1:01:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they were called colored,\Nstood up against the entire British Empire
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.23,1:01:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and defeated it.\NSpiritual strength, then, is of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.85,1:01:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not wimping out.\NIt's standing up for that which you know to be the reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.95,1:01:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So he stood up against the British Empire,\Ndefeated the entire British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.01,1:01:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't that knock you out?\NThis 90-pound skinny little guy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.01,1:01:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,knocked over the entire British Empire,\Nits sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.01,1:01:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That was very interesting historically.\NAnd Joel Goldsmith is an extremely well-known writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.43,1:01:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Manly Hall collected some really wonderful things.\NErnest Holmes is also in religious science.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.43,1:01:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And Vernon Howard.\NThese are all very well-known names.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.39,1:02:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Aldous Huxley, the great saints, Karmapa.\NI visited the Karmapa.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.45,1:02:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the presence of the Karmapa,\Nbut did not meet him personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.89,1:02:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Gopi Krishna, of course, his story is well-known.\NThis is one of the reasons I tell people,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.89,1:02:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,don't try to force the Kundalini.\NAnd Kriyananda, Brother Lawrence,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.31,1:02:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, is the prayer of the heart.\NBrother Lawrence, it's in a little booklet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.44,1:02:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was done, I think, in the 1600s.\NThe practice of the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.56,1:02:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to merely be constantly conscious\Nof the presence of God within.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.56,1:02:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A very powerful little book.\NAnd simplicity, without getting into any kind of thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.56,1:02:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,These are, of course, two are both well-known to us.\NNon-linear, Vedanta, the 700s.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.60,1:02:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Burton, extremely well-known.\NAnd here's Moses de Leon of Granada,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.60,1:03:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who was a rabbi at 720.\NAnd Mukherjee, I like his name, Mukherjee,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.60,1:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at 475.\NHave we got another slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.88,1:03:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the next slide?\NOr is that the last slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.24,1:03:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last slide.\NNo, we need the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.04,1:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two slides on spiritual teachers.\NWe did them both?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.22,1:03:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on now, you fool.\NOkay, let's go ahead then.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.83,1:03:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we were going to talk about,\Nyes, what keeps people stuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.83,1:03:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the book we're going to have out\Nat our next meeting, hopefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.89,1:03:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcending the Levels of Consciousness.\NSusan was one of the main inspirations for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.89,1:03:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, the do-it-ness, the do-it-ness.\NYou've got to write about the do-it-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.89,1:03:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we went back over the calibrated levels of consciousness\Nand looked at what is holding them in place.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.89,1:03:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they mean?\NUsually they're held in attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.96,1:04:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be spiritually free means\Nyou're not at the effect of attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.12,1:04:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither attractions nor aversions.\NAnd attractions and aversions are to,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.12,1:04:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,predominantly to the linear.\NMoney, no money. Health, no health.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.76,1:04:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wishing things to be different than they are.\NSo complete surrender at great depth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.04,1:04:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender at great depth\Nis the letting go of all attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.04,1:04:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you are completely free.\NYou're completely clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.24,1:04:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not run by attractions or aversions.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.49,1:04:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,here are the general,\Nthe attraction is in the left-hand column
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.49,1:04:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the aversion is in the right-hand column.\NMost people prefer control.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.48,1:04:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of giving up control is anathema.\NPlus it brings up all kinds of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.74,1:04:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of surrendering control\Nthen means
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.74,1:05:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go, having your life run by the ego.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.99,1:05:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the presumption is that you're alive because of the ego.\NAnd the truth is you're alive in spite of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.34,1:05:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That your survival is not based on the ego\Nbut the self with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.44,1:05:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the small self\Nthat tells you to look out
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.44,1:05:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and not run off the road.\NIt's because your self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.44,1:05:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is loving you to the degree that your small self\Npays attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.56,1:05:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the big self that your small self\Nremembers to take your vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.56,1:05:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for my ego,\NI wouldn't take my vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.56,1:05:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's because of your big self\Nthat your small self remembers
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.60,1:05:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've got to take your vitamins.\NSo the pleasure then is being in control
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.14,1:05:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're,\Nour whole society is,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.20,1:06:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all control freaks.\NEverybody has to control everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.20,1:06:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they don't,\Nit makes them feel uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.16,1:06:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncomfortable.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.05,1:06:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the anticipated pleasure of stuckness\Nis it's, it's, it's habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.05,1:06:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're familiar with it.\NAnd it's easier to hang in with what you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.47,1:06:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've been doing rather than change.\NWhich brings uncertainty and strangeness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.76,1:06:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember walking out of the house\Nwith no food and no money.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.76,1:06:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd written, of course, the miracles that all your,\Nall your needs would be provided for.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.01,1:06:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said,\Nwell, so it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.01,1:06:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure enough.\NAround lunchtime, somebody that I knew said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.01,1:06:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,did you have lunch yet?\NI said, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.01,1:06:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, yeah, I can't eat all this.\NAnd that's the way it went,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.01,1:06:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,around the clock, day after day.\NI never,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.01,1:06:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I literally saw anything.\NEverything happened,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.01,1:07:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous, just constantly presented.\NSo we want to stick in with,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.36,1:07:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for a feeling of control.\NActually, familiarity and habit
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.36,1:07:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you a feeling of control.\NBecause we're uncertain about what may happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.36,1:07:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to cling to the old\Ninstead of being afraid of the,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.36,1:07:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,this also seems to take effort.\NThe easy way is to stick with the old
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.91,1:07:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's hard.\NIt's easy to hate people,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.91,1:07:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to forgive them.\NWhy is it hard?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.00,1:07:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the resistance.\NIt isn't hard to forgive people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.52,1:07:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is the resistance,\Nthe clinging to wanting to be right
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.52,1:07:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanting them to be wrong.\NSo the,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.52,1:07:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these,\Nthe effort is not in
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.68,1:07:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these actual steps,\Nbut in overcoming the resistance to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.73,1:07:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People would rather ignore\Nand not look at a problem
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.73,1:07:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than look at it\Nbecause they might get upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.28,1:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, learn to enjoy being upset.\NIt's fun to be upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.28,1:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be real theatrical\Nand do your whole thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.28,1:08:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,stamp up and down, cry.\NIt's fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.69,1:08:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So go ahead and be upset, please.\NFor instance, I can't stop being upset
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.85,1:08:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tell them,\Nyour problem is you're not upset enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.85,1:08:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to get more upset.\NI want you to get more upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.85,1:08:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Cry harder, longer, gnash your teeth,\Nthrow yourself on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.85,1:08:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have a tantrum.\NBoom, boom, boom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.88,1:08:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon it runs out.\NIt runs out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.88,1:08:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NBecause when you choose to be this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.04,1:08:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then it loses its power over you.\NIt only has power
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.04,1:08:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when you ignore it.\NIgnoring and resisting it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.04,1:08:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,gives it energy.\NDisowning it, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.04,1:08:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is what we...\NWe want to disown things
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.17,1:08:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than take responsibility\Nbecause of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.33,1:08:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you look at what's blocking the thing,\Nwhat is the underlying feeling?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.33,1:08:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to take responsibility\Nbecause then I would feel guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.33,1:09:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then ask yourself,\Nyes, and why would you feel guilty?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.33,1:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you keep on doing it step by step\Nand eventually it falls apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.33,1:09:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what I'm talking about.\NI don't want to be upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.33,1:09:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take responsibility.\NAlways own what goes on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.28,1:09:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask what's within you.\NIf you hear a glass fall off the table,
