Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.54,1:20:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the creator divinity and God are at infinity.\NSo the highest degree that is possible to experience the presence of God in this earthly realm, then, is at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.29,1:20:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We call that incarnation.\NNow, the Buddha teaches...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.85,1:21:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the question is, enlightenment is always differentiated somewhat from, let's say, the state of Christ consciousness, which is divinity incarnate.\NWas the Buddha's ultimate state nothingness, as it's often quoted?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.35,1:21:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThis says, the Buddha experienced the allness, the infinite oneness, as divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.87,1:21:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, don't use the term divinity, because there's so much misinformation.\NThere's so much information about it, that you will send the person into a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.00,1:21:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid the word.\NBut he himself experienced, otherwise, the Buddha couldn't be at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.98,1:21:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Buddha nature, then, you see what's happening in the translation.\NHe says, don't use the term God, because you'll throw people into a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.87,1:21:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as the 12-step groups.\NYou talk about a higher power, because everybody's got some kind of a thing going about God.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.87,1:22:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Buddha was doing something similar.\NHe was saying, don't call it God.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.28,1:22:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He called it the Buddha's nature.\NThe Buddha nature is not voidness or nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.92,1:22:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's allness.\NAnd, therefore, the Buddha, like Christ or Krishna, experienced the presence of God as his own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.98,1:22:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's ever been said before.\NThe Buddha experienced the presence of God, much as I experienced.
