Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.82,1:31:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd so as...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.50,1:31:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is form.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.00,1:31:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't create form. It is form.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.64,1:31:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so as form or guilt arises, is there,\Nand as the presence arises,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.10,1:31:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is there a kind of transmutation that takes place?\NFrom the lower energy frequency to the higher,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.28,1:31:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with a kind of almost transmutation of coming out and letting go of resistance?\NIs there a transmutation of the lower to the higher?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.16,1:31:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the lower doesn't become the higher.\NIt's replaced by the higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.22,1:31:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBecause the initial response is based on perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.20,1:31:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And surrendering perception to God and asking to have the truth revealed to you,\Nremoves the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.59,1:31:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see the nonlinear.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.94,1:31:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the innocence,\Nthe basic innocence,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.84,1:31:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which the Course talks about,\Nbecomes apparent.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.68,1:32:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I like Socrates' statement,\Nbecause it makes it more apparent that everyone is innocent
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.84,1:32:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because they firmly believe that which they are pursuing.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.60,1:32:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd so responsibility is limited
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.64,1:32:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because the nature of the human mind is such that intrinsically,\Nit's unable to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.34,1:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NIt's not built for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.96,1:32:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not capable of it.\NAnd is there a physical desire to move this energy through the body in order to affect that?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.68,1:32:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in moving energies through the body.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.44,1:32:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.85,1:32:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want a picture breathing up the energy to a higher chakra,\Nthat's probably harmless.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.66,1:33:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the intention behind it, not the breathing itself.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.69,1:33:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Hawkins.\NOur study group has chosen the topic of, here, the energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.69,1:33:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility to discuss.\NAnd I was wondering if you could say something to us about radical humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.07,1:33:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know more about humility than anybody walking under your planet.\NAfter you've hit bottom, you know what humility means, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.74,1:33:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, humility really ensues from the reality of the understanding of the limitations of the human mind.\NIt isn't so much a spiritual prostration, you know, you're not spiritually prostrating yourself with ashes and sackcloth.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.93,1:34:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more just honesty.\NSo humility comes out of intrinsic honesty.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.32,1:34:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, you can't tell who's telling the truth.\NYou know, let's take something currently in the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.80,1:34:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no way of knowing it.\NWell, what's the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.32,1:34:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.\NUnless you're not a calibrator.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.94,1:34:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you know right away who's telling the truth.\NBut the mind, in and of itself, is not able to comprehend that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.34,1:34:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of accepting the reality comes the humility.\NOut of the reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.53,1:34:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That, to me, would be the highest form of acceptance.\NWould be through understanding the nature of the human mind, you automatically become humble.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.20,1:34:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you cannot tell truth from falsehood on its own.\NIt takes a jury of 12 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.73,1:35:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And they spend months.\NAnd at the end of that time, they don't know whether they're right or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.51,1:35:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, DNA testing.\NEveryone, DNA testing, they took off 165 people off death row across the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.75,1:35:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,165 people falsely condemned to death.\NAnd it was the wrong person.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.24,1:35:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And scientific research shows that visual identification in crime scenes is 50% an error.\NThey line people up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.13,1:35:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one that did it.\NThe chances are 50-50 that person is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.13,1:35:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,50-50.\NI'd hate to have my life hanging on 50-50, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.13,1:35:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With somebody that's nearsighted and was half-bombed at the time they looked at you.\NHe's the one.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.36,1:35:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My God.\NI remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.36,1:35:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So even under the best of circumstances, swearing an oath, the error is 50%.\NEven though somebody's life is hanging on.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.36,1:35:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm not saying that's a lie.\NI'm not saying that's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.36,1:35:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that's a lie.\NBut I'm saying that's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.36,1:35:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that's a lie.\NI'm not saying that's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.36,1:35:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that's a lie.\NI'm not saying that's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.36,1:35:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that's a lie.\NI'm not saying that's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.90,1:35:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that's a lie.\NI'm not saying that's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.94,1:35:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that's a lie.\NI don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.94,1:36:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.\NSo even under the best of circumstances, swearing an oath, the error is 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.36,1:36:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though somebody's life is hanging on it.\NSo that shows you how limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.30,1:36:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you see the limitation of the human mind, then humility is just an automatic consequence\Nof seeing what its limitation is.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.40,1:36:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't use a lawn mower to level a field.\NBecause it's just not capable of doing the job.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.77,1:36:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like when in your day, though, the ego is automatically in the knowing as you're coming across someone,\Nand humility is not something that enters your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.82,1:36:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, humility is like what I'm telling you about, contemplation.\NIt's part of one's attitude, that all information and everything you think are all presumptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.97,1:37:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all tentative.\NSo you hold thinkingness as tentative, but not as authoritative.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.56,1:37:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tentative. All evidence is tentative.\NPerception is just tentative evidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.98,1:37:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NIf you're going above 600 and you're leaving the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.16,1:37:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,would there be any possibility that you have to come back again and reincarnate?\NWould you have to come back again after hitting?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.18,1:37:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're on the level of 600, would you have to come back for any reason?\NNot for the reasons one would presume, not because it's a have-to due to negative karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.46,1:37:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not because you identify with the linear, but instead you see the options of the non-linear.\NSo it's a choice, I think, made between yourself and divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.98,1:38:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because friends of mine who are doing some kinesiologic testing got the Dramana Maharshi,\Nwas reincarnated and attended one of your lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.60,1:38:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember meeting him.\NSo it's not true?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.26,1:38:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know.\NHe said the world you see is illusion, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.66,1:38:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,although there's no point trying to save the world,\Nbecause the world you see doesn't even exist, you know, it's all in your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.37,1:38:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes humility to accept that.\NAnd it's only a belief system until it becomes true within one's own spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.43,1:38:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you see that all you're seeing is perception going,\Nall you're seeing is a run of perception, like TV images.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.33,1:39:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he never left that mountain.\NAnd I like Susan's sign too.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.80,1:39:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, my question is that today one of the students asked me if I would come up here and ask the question.\NAnd throughout the whole day I had severe anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.00,1:39:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to know, what is this anxiety?\NWhat is this anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.12,1:39:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is the most loving group on earth, and I'm in the presence of divinity in this group,\Nand yet I have this humongous anxiety to come up and ask a question and sit here and let people look at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.87,1:39:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NYou have to presume that you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.02,1:40:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to presume that you're safe.\NYou have to presume that everybody's thoughts about you are benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.82,1:40:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to presume that everybody's thoughts about you are benign.\NYou have to presume that everybody's happy that you're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.27,1:40:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NSo what you presume turns out to be a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.60,1:40:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's pleased that you're here and that you're speaking as you're speaking.\NI'm pleased.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.52,1:40:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you pleased?\NIt's stage anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.40,1:40:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stage fright.\NIt's stage fright.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.22,1:40:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NIt's stage fright.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.86,1:40:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I had stage fright when I was in kindergarten.\NWhen I was in kindergarten, they had a class play.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.84,1:40:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was supposed to be a rabbit.\NAnd I was supposed to hide behind this tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.86,1:40:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was a big cardboard tree.\NAnd on a cue, I was supposed to hop, hop, hop, hop, hop, hop, and then hop behind the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.30,1:40:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd I wouldn't come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.08,1:40:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.32,1:41:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd the cue lady kept saying, I didn't need to come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.92,1:41:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.72,1:41:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't.\NMy heart was beating fast, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.22,1:41:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.20,1:41:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Being looked at.\NBeing looked at.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.42,1:41:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's what it is.\NOther people looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.92,1:41:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NI want everybody to shut your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.86,1:41:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut your eyes.\NEverybody agree?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.40,1:41:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut your eyes.\NJust for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.80,1:41:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut your eyes.\NNobody's looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.06,1:41:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIs that better?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.98,1:41:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess not.\NBecause I think I'm looking at myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.64,1:41:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm judging myself every minute that possibly, you know, I'm not, well, I guess\NI put a value judgment on myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.80,1:41:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, imitate a person who has, what are we calling this issue, Scott?\NWhat have we been calling it before?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.71,1:41:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stage fright.\NStage fright.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.39,1:41:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.93,1:41:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitate a person who has stage fright.\NImitate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.16,1:42:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're not scared enough, you idiot.\NBecause I wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.49,1:42:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.07,1:42:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't stay calm, I'm going to kill you.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.89,1:42:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, the anxiety kind of released.\NI mean, I stood in line, it released a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.44,1:42:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And now.\NIt seemed like it released more.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.72,1:42:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, I don't know how, why, how, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.82,1:42:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You accepted the worst possible scenario, and you saw it was illusion.\NOh, is that what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.58,1:42:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.24,1:42:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NThe way to undo a fear or a phobia, or anything like that, keep going, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.58,1:42:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?\NThey're going to look at me, yeah, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.60,1:42:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they're going to laugh at me, and then what?\NAnd then they're going to think I'm stupid, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.00,1:42:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?\NAnd then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.80,1:42:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?\NAnd then I'll make a fool out of myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.56,1:42:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you keep accepting it.\NYou say, so I'm making a fool out of myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.92,1:42:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gives a, you know?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.24,1:43:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you accept the bottom line, it all goes away.\NThat's why eventually accepting the inevitability of death usually knocks about 95% of the other fears out of the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.62,1:43:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all of them are symbolic of physical death.\NI'll be poor, then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.72,1:43:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I won't have any money.\NThen I'll get kicked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.82,1:43:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I won't have any place to live.\NThen I'll starve to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.70,1:43:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?\NAnd it's always, and then I'll die.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.04,1:43:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you get down to the bedrock underneath all fears, it's the fear that I'll die.\NI'm not going to have everybody's approval here, therefore I'll die, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.58,1:43:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you, you know, the worst thing that's happened to you is you topple over right now.\NYou're not so lucky, you're still breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.80,1:43:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.36,1:43:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you so much, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.30,1:43:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this really helped me.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.84,1:43:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A great deal.\NYou're carried.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.16,1:43:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, and thank you, Susan.\NBye, Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.04,1:43:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NThis is lost music.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.38,1:43:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I took it, and I wanted you to sign it.\NOh, we'll send it back.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.88,1:43:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.60,1:44:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think facing stage fright is very hard.\NIt took a lot of courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.84,1:44:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.10,1:44:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so scared I forgot what she asked.\NI had to pray about what she was going to ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.25,1:44:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Susan.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.63,1:44:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That experience you spoke about this morning when you had the temptation that power,\Nthat power is yours, own it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.59,1:44:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That what?\NSorry, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.69,1:44:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience when you attempted that power is yours, all power is yours, own it.\NOwn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.79,1:44:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, yes.\NWhat calibration level does that occur at?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.04,1:44:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's probably over 850, yeah.\NOkay, I have permission to ask about the silent communication.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.52,1:44:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 800, 840, 850, 860.\NYeah, it comes in around 850 there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.10,1:45:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if the consciousness is still open,\Nto the Luciferic, at that calibration,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.65,1:45:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then wouldn't it be wise if one's intent was to go above that level?\NWell, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.57,1:45:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The person's aim is for enlightenment.\NBut enlightenment isn't that easily acquired.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.70,1:45:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And everywhere along the way there's a challenge.\NThat's the challenge there.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.96,1:45:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Christ sweat blood in the Garden of Eden.\NChrist sweat blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.30,1:45:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha felt like his bones were broken, see?\NSo, that which is the antithesis of truth sees you as a great danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.10,1:45:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you're an ordinary sinner and you go to church and all that crap, you're no nothing.\NAnd once you start really getting up there, you see what happens is your power is so enormous,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.80,1:45:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you become now a major threat.\NThe demons start looking for your weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.94,1:46:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fallen gurus, we once did a lecture on them,\Nthe temptation now comes in and finds the weakness in your armor.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.38,1:46:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexual seduction, flattery, money, having lots of followers, lots of wealth, pomp, circumstance.\NThe glamour of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.83,1:46:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner or later, they're going to find your weakness.\NThe pretty girl says, I love you, let's make love, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.08,1:46:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is holy, let's be holy.\NLet's have holy sex, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.58,1:46:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They fall into it right and left.\NSo, they look.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.07,1:46:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's due to lack of preparation at the lower level.\NIt's lack of a teacher warning you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.87,1:46:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel the teacher must teach you what the temptations are along the way\Nso that when you get there, you're not blindsided.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.65,1:46:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, my antipathy to the United States of America is its stupidity\Nin allowing itself to get blindsided about every 15 minutes about everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.68,1:47:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell are they doing?\NThey sound asleep up there or where are they, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.23,1:47:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so sound asleep that you don't know that there's a half a million\Ncommunists across the border in North Korea?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.34,1:47:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't know there's a half a million?\NI mean plain breathing.
